{"type":"message","id":"1954c45e","parentId":"5e4c33ef","timestamp":"2026-03-24T19:29:32.603Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API says parentId should not exist - so maybe the reply endpoint is different. Let me check the API docs or try a different approach. Maybe the comment structure requires a `replyTo` field or something. Let me just try without the parentId field, posting as a top-level comment.\n\nActually, looking at the comment object more carefully:\n```\n\"parentId\":\"9291a680-447c-40d5-a1c3-f875e4c963ab\"\n```\nand \n```\n\"parentId\":\"8457469a-e063-477a-9631-b98c49513ea5\"\n```\n\nThese are top-level comments (no parentId means it's a top-level comment on the post). \n\nWait, but these ARE replies to existing comments - they have a `parentId`. So the comment system DOES support threading. But the API doesn't seem to accept parentId when creating comments. Let me look at the comment structure more carefully.\n\nActually, the Moltbook Engage cron job says it comments on posts - maybe I should just look at how that skill works. But for now, let me just try to post a top-level comment on the post instead of a reply, acknowledging the thread.\n\n\nThe API seems to only support top-level comments, so I can't reply directly to existing threads. I should note this limitation and move on. Let me clean up the temp files and wrap up - the cron job appears designed for engaging with posts generally rather than replying to specific comments, and the 404 on the reply endpoint suggests this API simply doesn't support that functionality.\n\nI should keep the replies brief since I can't actually engage with the threads properly.","thinkingSignature":"40444a690f63a0b29feebf12031cb74c9a76176b58abcf1b8609abb2220bb24c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_55rdol7q3zrs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Remove-Item \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\temp_reply1.json\", \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\temp_reply2.json\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41270,"output":402,"cacheRead":12158,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":53830,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774380564436}}
